            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>That’s how much of a reduction in COVID spread can be achieved through:</p><ul><li>6 air changes per hour (ACH) of ventilation +</li><li>Upper room UVGI +</li><li><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/CorsiRosenthalBox">#CorsiRosenthalBox</a></li></ul><p>No mandates required.</p><p>Where did that number come from?</p><p><strong>75% reduction in transmission of measles </strong><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2789813/"><strong>from upper room UVGI</strong></a><strong>.</strong> 25% remains.</p><p><strong>50% reduction in transmission of measles from ventilation/filtration.</strong> 50% of these remain.</p><h3>Joseph Allen on Twitter: &quot;You&#39;re not going to believe this, but guess what works against measles?Our study--&gt; &quot;highlights primary importance of vaccination&quot;--&gt; &quot;additional and significant risk reduction can be achieved thru enhancing building ventilation and filtration systems&quot;https://t.co/BoWrBlleH4 https://t.co/vEX2JWiBgq / Twitter&quot;</h3><p>You&#39;re not going to believe this, but guess what works against measles?Our study--&gt; &quot;highlights primary importance of vaccination&quot;--&gt; &quot;additional and significant risk reduction can be achieved thru enhancing building ventilation and filtration systems&quot;https://t.co/BoWrBlleH4 https://t.co/vEX2JWiBgq</p><p><strong>25% * 50% of cases remaining = 12.5% total remaining = 87.5 % reduction.</strong></p><p>These methods work better together — better air circulation makes upper room UVGI more effective. CR Box addition mixes air even more and removes all PM2.5, not just virus laden aerosols.</p><p>87.5% reduction in COVID transmission from ventilation, filtration and upper room UVGI?! Am I too optimistic? Too much faith in engineering measures?</p><p>Fine. <em>Run some RCTs and prove me wrong.</em></p><p><em>Originally published at </em><a href="https://www.itsairborne.com/tweets/engineering-methods/my-number/index.html"><em>https://www.itsairborne.com</em></a><em> on March 6, 2022.</em></p><img src="https://medium.com/_/stat?event=post.clientViewed&referrerSource=full_rss&postId=b28db8555144" width="1" height="1" alt=""><hr><p><a href="https://itsairborne.com/heres-my-number-87-5-b28db8555144">Here’s my number: 87.5%</a> was originally published in <a href="https://itsairborne.com">It’s Airborne</a> on Medium, where people are continuing the conversation by highlighting and responding to this story.</p>]]></content:encoded>
